			<!-- Begin News/Information Section -->
				<table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" ID="Table23">
					<tr id="trmasthead">
						<td valign="middle" class="main_font" align="center">
							<font size="3"><b>&nbsp;</b></font>
					    </td>
					</tr>
					
					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Magician Guide</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:xylix@undienet.org">elixir</a> | 
		            4/7/1999 10:52:43 AM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">So, you're gonna be a Magician, eh?  Well, as a newbie Magician you may seem discouraged at first, but as you progress, your skills and abilitys and immense power will begin to shine, and believe me, you will enjoy it very much.<BR>
<BR>
The very first thing you need to do as a magician, is obviously, take your Guild note to your guild, and find the bank and store your PK note in it. (You definitly dont want to be +PvP at level 1 :)<BR>
Head on out to your local newbie hunting ground, equip your Dagger, scribe your beginning spells,(Burst of Flame and Minor shielding), memorize them, then head on out!  As a beginner, always make sure you know exactly where you are, and where you're heading.  It is extremely frustrating to plunge into a battle before you realize that you are overmatched.  In cases like these, RUN.  Yes, thats right, RUN like you've never ran before.  Where do you run?  To the nearest guard, obviously.  Once you have acquired a mere couple gold, return to your guild and purchase summon food, and summon drink.  That will save money, as well as allow you to hunt longer, without having to return to the nearest merchant to purchase goods.  <BR>
<BR>
After much hard work, you reach level 4 and you think &quot;So whats so good about Magicians?&quot;.  Answer:  Elementals :).<BR>
<BR>
You have 4 types of elementals, each with their own strengths and weaknesses, and you get new ones every 4 levels, which get increasinly stronger and are higher levels.<BR>
<BR>
The four types:<BR>
Fire elementals are the best offensive fighters, but they lack HP.<BR>
Air has an average strength attack, with a fairly low delay, but they periodically cast Invisibility on themselves.<BR>
Water elementals have Average Offense, and Average defense, with a moderate amount of Hp's, yet they have extremely high AC.<BR>
Earth elementals, well, In my opinion are far superior to all others.  They have approximatly 50-75% MORE health than Water elementals, with an average offense and defense, and quite possibly a better taunt.  My obvious preferance.  :)<BR>
<BR>
Your elementals gain abilitys, much like a warrior.  Riposte, Dodge, Double Attack.  They are very potent later on.  Keep in mind that your elementals do not get stronger as you gain levels, they are as strong as the spell level.  IE: If you have a level 8 earth elemental spell, once its summoned it will be anywhere from 7, 8, or 9.  So /consider your elemental when its summoned, and determine what level it is so you do not rush into a difficult battle with a weak elemental, only to discover he is no match and you will soon be fleeing.  You also share a small bit of EXP with your elemental, but the rate at which you can hunt definitly makes up for it, considering you dont have to sit healing all the time like a warrior, or whatnot :).<BR>
<BR>
You may also think that your Offensive spells are not powerful enough.  You must realize that the Magician isn't all about direct damage spells, its balanced with the Elementals.  If you want &quot;nuke&quot; spells, play a wizard.  Although your spells later on will be rather potent, such as Shock of Blades, which is a level 8 spell, and does approximatly 40 damage, and has minimal Mana usage.<BR>
<BR>
Magicians are also well reputed, because of their practical spells.  Its always great to hand a friend some freshly summoned bread and water, or even a Wisp Stone, dagger, or Spears!  It can save much time and money not having to purchase these items at stores.  Serve your people well, and they will have utmost respect for you.  (Not only that, but you can make money too! he he)  However, keep in mind that they only remain until you either log out, or die.  <BR>
<BR>
Thanks for reading these vital Magician secrets, and may your adventures be enjoyable, and without deaths.  :)<BR>
<BR>
                   elixir
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
