				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hmmm all this talk of the best pets to use... I find that the pets each work best based on the situation. Earth for soloing (rooted enemy cant hit you while you nuke it), Water for outdoor group fighting where the tanks keep the mobs off ya, Fire works bets for me indoor group fighting b/c  of the damage that baby delivers I must add these are my preferences but the fire/water elems work on both of these situations, and lets not forget the air. Against casters an air is the way to go it is extremely fast and casts stun as well it will keep that emeny mob from healing the other ones. This is very inportant when facing caster type mobs it really sucks to use 60% of your mana to almost kill a monster then watch it get healed all the way up by a caster monster 8(. Hope this helps some. Btw we got a new type of monster to summon now at level 34 you get summon monster 1 i understand this to summon a randome creature from the zone you are in as your pet. i saw a mage in oasis with a SG for a pet 8). Other things i discovered stick to 1hb from the beginning all of your focus items are nice 1hb weapons + buffing your pets and our epic quest is a 1hb of godly power 8). I am level 30 now and i used piercing alot so now I have my focus items and such i really suck in melee ( I know I know we dont melee well but sometimes you gotta). Plus you get free skills! Summon bandages and practice that skill as much as possible will pay oiff later. And learn to throw daggers wen you can summon daggers the skill is free. and later when your oom and your pet is whacking the mob you can do 10pt adm with those i do, besides its fun heehee. Enjoy yourself with all the fun i have  i dont see why there arent more mages around.<BR>
