			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				All these Mage posts, and nobody has yet mentioned chain casting.  Well, here goes...  a strat that, if performed correctly, can help you take out yellow or even red cons without a scratch (at the cost of much Malachite, however).<BR>
<BR>
First off, the Earth pet is the best to do this with because of his root.  You can do it with the others, but you need to get the timing down just right.<BR>
<BR>
Here's what you do:<BR>
Send in your pet (+Fireshield, Burnout, whatever), target it so you can see its health and then sit down and meditate.  Keep an eye on its health, and when you see it getting low (around 35% or so), stand up and begin summoning a new pet.  While the spell is being cast, type /pet get lost (don't hit enter yet) and wait until the casting is almost complete.  Then hit enter, dismissing your current pet and allowing your new pet to come forth.  Now send your freshly-summoned pet after the mob.  If you're using the Earth pet, the thing should be rooted so it won't even have a chance to smack you around while you're getting your new pet ready.  Shield and Burnout your pet, rinse and repeat.<BR>
<BR>
At level 11, I can easily take out yellow cons in Lavastorm with this tactic.<BR>
<BR>
__________<BR>
Mrazyk<BR>
Dark Elf Magician<BR>
Clan Darkfire, Povar Server
