	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have a little suggestion for any Mages that would like to quickly get through lvl 20 to 24.<BR>
<BR>
Go to High Keep (Its near Kith forest). Go to the lookout room if its not taken. You will need an Earth pet for this, make sure its as high a lvl as possible(Malachite is sold here so thats not a prob) 2 Goblins will spawn in this room every 12 minutes. Breaking the room can be tricky (ask for some help) If timed properly you should have one Gob spawn every 6 minutes, which I found to be just enough time to med back to full. <BR>
<BR>
Heres what you do:<BR>
1) Sit at the far end of the room <BR>
2) Fire shield pet<BR>
3) Send in pet<BR>
4) NUKENUKENUKE<BR>
The Gob will aggro on you and probably break your pets root, at that time run around till it is rooted again and nuke it again.<BR>
<BR>
There are several reasons for doing this, one Gobs have weak fire resist, and at that lvl you are using a fire based DD spell. Two, it is a controlled spawn meaning you dont have to run around looking for targets. Three, I have never before or since been able to solo a RED con, yes RED. THe exp is amazing! 1/4 bub per kill at lvl 20! Simply amazing!!!<BR>
<BR>
Unfortunatly this is very risky, I died several times doing this, but the rewards are worth it.<BR>
I went from 20 to 24 in two days. Hardly had a chance to try out my 20 line of spells hehe.<BR>
<BR>
This isnt for everyone, but I think every mage should try it.<BR>
<BR>
Good luck (and remember the guards are close in this zone  :-)  )<BR>
<BR>
P.S. As for the ongoing pet debate, I personnaly like them all :)<BR>
<BR>
Torvakk Bolas<BR>
40th Magician <BR>
Tarew Marr <BR>

