	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hello I just have a couple of things to add.<BR>
<BR>
First, magician's bandaging skill maxes at 100 :(<BR>
Second, yes all the pets are useful in different situations.<BR>
<BR>
On the earth pet's root:<BR>
<BR>
This was less of an issue before the recent patch, but now it has become more important.  When the Mob you are fighting begins to run away and it is rooted, it will turn around and fight, otherwise it will run until your pet kills it.  This is why you may want to pick a water, air, or fire elemental while fighting outdoors, or in a dungeon where the runner wont bring back friends that will kill you.<BR>
<BR>
If you are fighting an undead or group of undead that will 1. never run away and 2. Attack the nearest mob they hate: Use earth, damage shield, send in to attack, alternate nuke and heal.<BR>
<BR>
Finally, if you find yourself taking an unacceptable amount of damage during a battle, by all means use the earth pet's root to help keep the mob off you.  This is especially true with SoWed mobs that tend to ignore the pet(the guard up by lavastorm was a good example that was used before)<BR>
<BR>
On kiting:<BR>
<BR>
I haven't noticed that the fire pet deals significantly more melee damage or spell damage.  The extra damage on the Fire Ele comes from its massive damage shield.  If your kiting methods work correctly the mob should not be hitting the fire pet very often, making the water or air pet the preferred choice in this situation.<BR>
<BR>
Air vs. Earth:<BR>
<BR>
So the air has higher defense but less hp than the earth pet(the stun adds even more to this defense, as mobs dont attack while stunned).  The benefits of this that no one has mentioned is that healing spells are much more effective.  in the time it takes to get each pet down to half, you might cast, say, 3 spells.  2 Nukes and a heal.  The air pet will be once again near to full hp, while the earth will be maybe 75% (I'm useing arbitrary numbers, I'm not sure of the actual values)  This means your heal spell is much more efficient on the air pet.  The main tradeoffs are that the damage shield will hit less and if you get unlucky rolls the air pet might die unexpectedly.<BR>
<BR>
I have read that pets will wear aromor you give them, and recieve AC benfits from said armor.  I haven't tested this myself, but you may want to give that cloth armor to your pet if you dont need the extra gold...<BR>
<BR>
Finally, the sword of runes procs on everything for any NPC at any level, not just pets.  I haven't tried this on a rat or a mob that doesnt visably equip weapons, but I put a sword of runes on Guard Cheslin in qeynos hills.  Guard Cheslin is about level 4 I think and the sword proc'd for him.  He actually had a chance for once against the Large Bats :)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
