	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Reiksguard makes a few excellent points what pet you use is totally based on how you plan on playing them, i'll use completly different pets in different zones or situations, but i'd have to this is my basic rule of thumb, Solo outside without a doubt i use water, they do last quite a bit longer on melee mobs, and really dish out a good amount of damage, 2nd highest str/dex 2nd highest hp, 2nd highest dd. it doesn't have many of the flaws of the other pets and works pretty consistantly, also they heal much quicker than earth pets, with earth pets i have to wait an aditional minute to heal and med it after the fight with water i do not... Earth pets are great when working with another player (except for a necro cause the root messes with their spells) if you're camping casters in a group air is great cause their stuns very effectively stop mobs from casting, (it's stun spell doesn't seem to be resisted quite as much as earths root) if you're camping melee mobs in a group go with earth hopefully with enough people you massacre you're target before you're pet or anyone else is signifigantly damaged.  Fire pets are great in large groups as they aren't attacked quite as much and their direct damage spell can be quite deadly.   As for summoned items and the such they can be quite handy if you use em, you'll figure out a few uses for them besides they make you're pet hit with magic damage (wisps, ghouls, ect) a staff that has a charge of Cancel magic is great to give to say a tank class, since if they are dotted they have a means to take it off, or they can take a dot off somebody unconscience or charmed, or feared even. Once you're pet is 24 always equip'em with 2 weapons so that they duel weild, when you get the spell summon rune swords, ALWAYS use rune swords as they proc quite often for 40dmg (only for pets it seems) against any mob (not just summoned ones as the effect discription implies) and while you will eventually make pets that hit for over 40 dmg, they dont always hit for 40+ so for the most part the extra second it takes them to &quot;cast&quot; the proc is worth it, given to about 4-6 pets in you're group mobs are hacked and slashed rather quickly...  Bandages are also very important make sure you work on this skill not only does it save you/others from dying from poison and most dots, but after a fight you health comes back slower than you're mana so if you're below 50 with health bandage up and make sure you're phantom series of spells are on (gives you more hitpoints per tick with the buff on) and by the time you hit full mana you wont be waiting for the health to catch up... If you're grouped with a warrior, give em some bandages without them asking and bandage them after a fight if they need it, a healthy tank is a happy tank (to my knowledge my bandage skill is temporarily maxed out till like 55 i think and heals 35 hit points over the time of 2 ticks or 12 seconds, with 2+ people using the skill even the biggest baddest tank will be walking around in no time.
				</font>
			</td>

